      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Evert Glebbeek</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"https://astro.ru.nl/wiki/nl/general/people/evert_glebbeek\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/9/93/EvertGlebbeek.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"253\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:EvertGlebbeek.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Evert Glebbeek <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Evert Glebbeek</b>,<br />\na Dutch astrophysicist at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radboud_University_Nijmegen\">Radboud Universiteit Nijmegen</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and before at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McMaster_University\">McMaster University</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamilton,_Ontario\">Hamilton, Ontario</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canada\">Canada</a>. \nAs avocational games and chess programmer, Evert Glebbeek is author of the <a href=\"/Category:Open_Source\" title=\"Category:Open Source\">open source engines</a> <a href=\"/Jazz\" title=\"Jazz\">Jazz</a>, <a href=\"/Sjaak_(Glebbeek)\" title=\"Sjaak (Glebbeek)\">Sjaak</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Leonidas&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Leonidas (page does not exist)\">Leonidas</a>, all under the terms of the <a href=\"/Free_Software_Foundation#GPL\" title=\"Free Software Foundation\">GNU General Public Licence</a>. \nSjaak and Leonidas are able to play various chess variants <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, Sjaak not to confused with <a href=\"/Ronald_de_Man\" title=\"Ronald de Man\">Ronald de Man's</a> engine with the same name <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#2006_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2006 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2011_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2011 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evert_Glebbeek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2006_...\">2006 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evert_Glebbeek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 2006 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=155509\">Robert G. Izzard</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a> (<b>2006</b>). <i>Window To The Stars</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Astronomy_(journal)\">New Astronomy</a>, Vol. 12, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/astro-ph/0607611\">arXiv:astro-ph/0607611</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.ast.cam.ac.uk/~rgi/window.html\">Window To The Stars by Robert Izzard and Evert Glebbeek</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://adsabs.harvard.edu/full/2008IAUS..246..363G\">Building Blue Stragglers with Stellar Collisions</a></i>. Dynamical Evolution of Dense Stellar Systems, Proceedings of the International Astronomical Union, IAU Symposium, Volume 246, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0710.1730\">arXiv:0710.1730</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>When Stars Collide</i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Unsolved-Problems-Stellar-Physics-Astrophysics/dp/0735404623\">Unsolved Problems in Stellar Physics</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0710.1734\">arXiv:0710.1734</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.aanda.org/articles/aa/abs/2008/36/aa09931-08/aa09931-08.html\">Evolution of stellar collision products in open clusters. II. A grid of low-mass collisions</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_%26_Astrophysics\">Astronomy and Astrophysics</a>, Vol. 488, No. 3, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0806.0865\">arXiv:0806.0865</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.narcis.nl/publication/RecordID/oai:dspace.library.uu.nl:1874%2F27801/Language/nl\">Evolution of the Remnants of Stellar Collisions</a></i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utrecht_University\">Utrecht University</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Simon_Portegies_Zwart\" title=\"Simon Portegies Zwart\">Simon Portegies Zwart</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pid/36/4136.html\">Steve McMillan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=30pFuQgAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Breanndán Ó Nualláin</a>, Douglas Heggie, James Lombardi, Piet Hut, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://astro.uni-bonn.de/~sambaran/\">Sambaran Banerjee</a>, Houria Belkus, Tassos Fragos, John Fregeau, Michiko Fuji, <a href=\"/Mathematician#EGaburov\" title=\"Mathematician\">Evghenii Gaburov</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, Derek Groen, Stefan Harfst, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.org/pid/32/1525.html\">Rob Izzard</a>, Mario Juric, Stephen Justham, Peter Teuben, Joris van Bever, Ofer Yaron, Marcel Zemp (<b>2008</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-540-69387-1_23\">A Multiphysics and Multiscale Software Environment for Modeling Astrophysical Systems</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.iccs-meeting.org/iccs2008/\">ICCS 2008</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lecture_Notes_in_Computer_Science\">Lecture Notes in Computer Science</a>, Vol. 5102, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0807.1996\">arXiv:0807.1996</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#EGaburov\" title=\"Mathematician\">Evghenii Gaburov</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selma_de_Mink\">Selma E. de Mink</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a>, <a href=\"/Simon_Portegies_Zwart\" title=\"Simon Portegies Zwart\">Simon Portegies Zwart</a> (<b>2009</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.aanda.org/articles/aa/abs/2009/13/aa10425-08/aa10425-08.html\">The evolution of runaway stellar collision products</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_%26_Astrophysics\">Astronomy and Astrophysics</a>, Vol. 497, No. 1, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0902.1753\">arXiv:0902.1753</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evert_Glebbeek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.ca/citations?user=-tDmx-kAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Alison Sills</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://inspirehep.net/record/852895\">Multiple Populations in Globular Clusters: The Possible Contributions of Stellar Collisions</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monthly_Notices_of_the_Royal_Astronomical_Society\">Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society</a>, Vol. 407, No. 1, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1004.4166\">arXiv:1004.4166</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=155509\">Robert G. Izzard</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.de/citations?user=BkQIoswAAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Richard J. Stancliffe</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a> (<b>2012</b>). <i>The occurrence of nitrogen-enhanced metal-poor stars: implications for the initial mass function in the early Galactic halo</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_%26_Astrophysics\">Astronomy and Astrophysics</a>, Vol. 547, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1209.6082\">arXiv:1209.6082</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#EGaburov\" title=\"Mathematician\">Evghenii Gaburov</a>, <a href=\"/Simon_Portegies_Zwart\" title=\"Simon Portegies Zwart\">Simon Portegies Zwart</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#ORPols\" title=\"Mathematician\">Onno R. Pols</a> (<b>2013</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://academic.oup.com/mnras/article/434/4/3497/964355\">Structure and evolution of high-mass stellar mergers</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monthly_Notices_of_the_Royal_Astronomical_Society\">Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society</a>, Vol. 434, No. 4, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1307.2445\">arXiv:1307.2445</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evert_Glebbeek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2011_...\">2011 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evert_Glebbeek&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2011 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=37831\">Material imbalance/bad trade and borrowing code</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 27, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Material\" title=\"Material\">Material</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=38084\">Attack and mobility evaluation in chess variants</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 15, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Mobility\" title=\"Mobility\">Mobility</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=405608&amp;t=38963\">Re: Castling legality check</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 03, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Castling\" title=\"Castling\">Castling</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>2012</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=44844\">Reductions from internal iterative deepening</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 20, 2012&#160;» <a href=\"/Reductions\" title=\"Reductions\">Reductions</a>, <a href=\"/Internal_Iterative_Deepening\" title=\"Internal Iterative Deepening\">Internal Iterative Deepening</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=45460\">How to make evaluation different for new program</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 05, 2012</li></ul>\n<p><b>2013</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=47622\">Causes for inconsistent benchmark signatures</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 27, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/En_passant\" title=\"En passant\">En passant</a>, <a href=\"/Forsyth-Edwards_Notation\" title=\"Forsyth-Edwards Notation\">Forsyth-Edwards Notation</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=47632\">The value of a pawn</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 28, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/Point_Value\" title=\"Point Value\">Point Value</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=47713\">An experiment with material imbalances and game-phase</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Evert Glebbeek</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 06, 2013&#160;» <a href=\"/Material_Tables\" title=\"Material Tables\">Material Tables</a></li>\n<l